- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - SECOND CALL FOR PAPERS 1999 IEEE Knowledge and Data Engineering Exchange Workshop Sponsored by the IEEE Computer Society Co-located with the 11 th IEEE Tools with Artificial Intelligence Conference November 8 , 1999 , Chicago , Illinois http : / / kdex 99 . eecs . uic . edu - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - IMPORTANT DATES July 20 , 1999 Deadline for submission of extended abstracts September 7 , 1999 Notification of acceptance / rejection October 7 , 1999 Deadline for submission of camera-ready copies - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - SCOPE OF WORKSHOP The 1999 IEEE Knowledge and Data Engineering Exchange Workshop ( KDEX'99 ) will provide an international forum for researchers , educators and practitioners to exchange and evaluate information and experiences related to state-of-the-art issues and trends in the areas of artificial intelligence and databases . The goal of this workshop is to expedite technology transfer from researchers to practitioners , to assess the impact of emerging technologies on current research directions , and to identify emerging research opportunities . The theme of the workshop is "AI MEETS DATABASES". Topics of interest include , but are not limited to : * Computer supported cooperative processing and interoperable systems * Data sharing , data warehousing and meta -data management * Distributed intelligent mediators and agents * Human-agent interaction and virtual information spaces * Distributed object management * Information structures and information brokering * Intelligent search , data mining and content-based retrieval * Hypertext and Web information organization * Management of incomplete and uncertain information * Knowledge and data engineering systems * Quality assurance for knowledge and data engineering systems * Software re-engineering and intelligent software information systems * Spatio-temporal , active , mobile and multimedia data * Electronic commerce - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - SUBMISSION GUIDELINES Authors are invited to submit an extended abstract not exceeding 6 pages ( single-spaced , 11 pt minimum , approximately 3000 words ) by July 20 , 1999 . Electronic submissions are required . Please send an e-mail containing your submission in Postscript , PDF or plain text format to : bastani @ cvc . bbli . ips Authors are required to send an "intention to submit" by July 13 , 1999 to bastani @ vef . dvt . rj . This should consist of an e-mail containing the title , authors , short abstract ( 100 words ) and main topic of the paper . Please address inquiries to : peters @ qe . pdg . xi
The KDEX'99 Program Committee will evaluate each submission on the basis of originality , accuracy , clarity and significance of results . Papers accepted for presentation will be published in the workshop proceedings by the IEEE Computer Society . A selected number of the accepted papers will be considered for publication in the IEEE Transactions on Knowledge and Data Engineering . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - WORKSHOP ORGANIZATION Steering Committee : C .
